== Pickled Shallot ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and halve @Mini Cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Season tomato and cucumber with a pinch of @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Halve @Lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and very thinly slice @Shallot{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Remove and discard any large stems from @Kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Roughly chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from half the lemon, 1 TBSP water, ½ tsp @Sugar{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper (use juice from one whole lemon, 2 TBSP water, and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Stir in shallot.

Cover #bowl{} with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside to pickle.

== Chickpeas ==

Meanwhile, drain and rinse @Chickpeas{1%400g can}; thoroughly pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Place chickpeas on a #baking sheet{}; arrange a large piece of plastic wrap on top. Lightly smash chickpeas with a #mallet{} or heavy-bottomed pan, breaking them apart.

> No need to pulverize—aim to keep the chickpeas somewhat intact.

Remove plastic wrap. To chickpeas on sheet, add a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tbsp}, @Cumin{1%tsp}, ¾ tsp @Paprika{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the paprika later.) Toss to combine; spread across sheet in a single layer.

Roast on top rack until crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}.

== Dressing ==

Remove plastic wrap from bowl with pickled shallot; drain shallot, reserving pickling liquid.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine garlic, @Tahini{4%tbsp}, @Yogurt{2%tbsp}, juice from remaining lemon, remaining @Paprika{1/4%tsp}, 1 TBSP olive oil, 1 TBSP pickling liquid, and ½ tsp sugar (2 TBSP olive oil, 2 TBSP pickling liquid, and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Add water 1 tsp at a time until dressing reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine kale and a drizzle of olive oil. Using your hands, massage until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

> Knead the kale leaves like dough.

To bowl with kale, add pickled shallot, tomato, cucumber, half the parsley, and half the dressing. Toss to combine.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with chickpeas and remaining parsley; drizzle with remaining dressing. Serve.